Folks,

Summary of IETF Internet-Drafts we have recently revised:

Title:     Security Assessment of Neighbor Discovery (ND) for IPv6
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gont-opsec-ipv6-nd-security-01.txt>


Title:     Security Implications of IPv6 options of Type 10xxxxxx
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gont-6man-ipv6-smurf-amplifier-01.txt>


Title:     Security Implications of Predictable Fragment
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gont-6man-predictable-fragment-id-03.txt>


Title:     Processing of IPv6 "atomic" fragments
URL:
http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-6man-ipv6-atomic-fragments-03.txt


Title:     Security Implications of IPv6 on IPv4 Networks
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-ipv6-implications-on-ipv4-nets-02.txt>


Title:     Recommendations on filtering of IPv4 packets containing IPv4
options
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-ip-options-filtering-01.txt>


Title:     Network Reconnaissance in IPv6 Networks
URL:
http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-ipv6-host-scanning-00.txt


Title:     Virtual Private Network (VPN) traffic leakages in dual-stack
hosts/ networks
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-vpn-leakages-00.txt>


Title:     DHCPv6-Shield: Protecting Against Rogue DHCPv6 Servers
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-dhcpv6-shield-00.txt>


Title:     Security Implications of IPv6 Fragmentation with IPv6
Neighbor Discovery
URL:
<http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-6man-nd-extension-headers-02.txt>


